      "text": [
        " : سُئِلَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ وَ أَنَا حَاضِرٌ عَنِ اَلْمَرْأَةِ تُحْرِمُ فِي اَلْعِمَامَةِ وَ لَهَا عَلَمٌ قَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2640 - It was narrated from Abu al-Hasan al-Nahdi, who said:\nAbu Abdullah (as) was asked, while I was present, about a woman entering Ihram wearing a turban (imamah) with an emblem (alam).\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
